 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Field Glass Implemenation Consultant Capgemini 8,227 reviews Burbank, CA Capgemini 8,227 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Contract Full Job Description Duration :8+Months 
Responsibilities : 
Facilitation of as-is and to-be business process discussions with customer subject matter experts to enable translation into to-be functional process flow documentation 
Accountable for Quality of Requirements gathering and functional solution design 
Works with an assigned Project Manager to present best practices workflows to client, and appropriately responds to clients? business problems 
Perform user requirements analysis; facilitate business process design sessions, identify gaps, issues and reporting risk areas as part of a software implementation delivery team 
Translates client business processes and requirements into business process flow documentation, solution design to support customer's desired to-be state 
Primary point of contact on all business design deliverables, and provides solution design advise and support as needed to support the completion of the deliverables 
Responds to client requests by performing appropriate tests to determine if ideas work; communicates results back to client along with possible alternative solutions 
During analysis engages more technical design Fieldglass SME?s to validate the functional design requirements captured which will enable a solution that meets the client?s requirements 
To support functional design; needs to understand and manage how data is mapped and how data decisions should align with business decisions being gathered and made. 
Requirements : 
Responsible for ensuring the client provides the relevant data in line with functional and technical requirements to support the solution and owns the management of the data in the client system 
Trains the client SMEs to complete the data import templates 
Works in tandem with the other Fieldglass work stream specialists (finance, reporting, integration, and configuration) to correctly map out data requirements for their work streams 
Coordinates and collaborates with Fieldglass SME?s and teams to ensure all requirements are fully captured, documented and signed off and aligned with all work streams ? including Finance, Integrations, Reporting etc. 
Ensures that design decisions of all Fieldglass work streams are aligned 
Translates documented and signed-off functional business processes and requirements into a technical design, and system configurations to support customer's desired to-be state 
Ensures the system works as designed together with other work stream leads and more technical design Fieldglass SME?s 
Manages all aspects of the technology set-up from base configuration to the designed client system, including all ticket related activities 
Before commencing client user acceptance testing, checks all configured elements requested by client and ensures all business requirements are correctly accounted for in the set up 
Fully tests every required feature, function and workflow in the client application, including an E2E in order to support other work streams deliverables when applicable 
Manages the set-up of user acceptance testing including the staging of data. 
Assists with the delivery and coordination of user acceptance testing with the client and MSP where applicable 
Ensures that any issues (Data and application) raised during testing are coordinated and resolved 
